  "content_id": "4254ac91-adab-445f-af54-0ff03b5826e7",
  "description": "Check current river conditions, restrictions and facilities",
  "details": {
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "hide_chapter_navigation": false,
    "parts": [
      {
        "body": "<h2 id=\"check-river-levels\">Check river levels</h2>\n\n<p>You can check current:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://check-for-flooding.service.gov.uk/river-and-sea-levels\">river levels in England</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://naturalresources.wales/evidence-and-data/maps/check-river-levels/?lang=en\">river levels in Wales</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.sepa.org.uk/environment/water/water-levels/\">water levels in Scotland</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.infrastructure-ni.gov.uk/topics/rivers-and-flooding/rivers-and-lough-levels\">rivers and lough levels in Northern Ireland</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"strong-stream-warnings\">Strong stream warnings</h2>\n\n<p>The Environment Agency gives out stream warnings to tell you about conditions that may mean you should not go out in your boat. You may also see red flags at boat clubs.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/guidance/river-thames-current-river-conditions\">Check the current conditions on the River Thames</a> - they’re published online every day by 11am.</p>\n\n<p>You can check strong stream warnings for other rivers by calling the phone line.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p>Strong stream advice<br>\nTelephone: 0345 988 1188  <br>\n24 hour service <br>\n<a href=\"/call-charges\">Find out about call charges</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Choose option 1 when your call is answered and enter the quick dial code for one of the following rivers:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>River Nene - 032112</li>\n  <li>Great Ouse (Bedford to St Ives) – 033211</li>\n  <li>Great Ouse (St Ives to Earith) – 033212</li>\n  <li>Ancholme - 031212</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can also sign up to the strong stream advice messaging system for the Rivers Nene, Great Ouse and Ancholme (it’s free).</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p>Strong stream advice messaging system<br>\nTelephone: 020 3025 5068<br>\n<a href=\"/call-charges\">Find out about call charges</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2 id=\"check-tide-predictions\">Check tide predictions</h2>\n\n<p>You can read <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.ukho.gov.uk/easytide/EasyTide/index.aspx\">tide predictions for the next 7 days</a> for rivers in England and Wales.</p>\n\n<p>You can also check:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://pla.co.uk/Safety/Tidal-information\">live and predicted tides on the tidal Thames</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/government/publications/rye-harbour-tide-times\">tide predictions at Rye Harbour</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://easytide.ukho.gov.uk/EasyTide/EasyTide/ShowPrediction.aspx?PortID=0109E&amp;PredictionLength=7\">tide predictions for Allington Lock on the River Medway</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "river-levels-and-warnings",
        "title": "River levels and warnings"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You can check the following for the non-tidal River Thames, which is managed by the Environment Agency:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/river-thames-current-river-conditions\">current conditions on the River Thames</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/guidance/river-thames-conditions-closures-restrictions-and-lock-closures\">river closures and restrictions</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/government/collections/river-thames-detail-for-closures-restrictions-and-lock-closures\">lock closures</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/government/publications/river-thames-emergency-rendezvous-points\">emergency rendezvous points between Teddington and Lechlade</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can also check <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.pla.co.uk/Safety/Regulations-and-Guidance/Notices-to-Mariners/Notices-to-Mariners\">current works and closures</a> on the tidal Thames, which is managed by the Port of London Authority.</p>\n\n<p>You should read the <a href=\"/government/publications/river-thames-navigation-licensing-and-general-byelaws-1993\">navigation bylaws</a> and <a href=\"/government/publications/river-thames-registration-byelaws-1953\">registration bylaws</a> before you set out.</p>\n\n<p>You can also check:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>information about <a href=\"/river-thames-bridges-locks-and-facilities-for-boaters\">bridges, locks and facilities for boaters</a>\n</li>\n  <li>the <a href=\"/government/publications/river-thames-and-connecting-waterways-cruising-guide\">River Thames and connecting waterways: cruising guide</a>\n</li>\n  <li>Port of London Authority information about <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.boatingonthethames.co.uk/\">boating on the Thames</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "river-thames",
        "title": "River Thames"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You can <a href=\"/river-medway-conditions-closures-and-restrictions\">check conditions, closures and restrictions on the River Medway</a> (updated during business hours - Monday to Friday, 9am to 5pm).</p>\n\n<p>You can telephone Allington Lock for the latest information outside of business hours.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p>Allington Lock<br>\nTelephone: 01622 752864<br>\n<a href=\"/call-charges\">Find out about call charges</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You should read the navigation bylaws for the <a href=\"/government/publications/river-medway-byelaws\">Upper Medway</a> and <a href=\"/government/publications/environment-agency-land-drainage-and-sea-defence-byelaws\">Southern Region</a>.</p>\n\n<p>You can also read the <a href=\"/government/publications/river-medway-a-users-guide\">user’s guide to River Medway</a>.</p>\n",
        "slug": "river-medway",
        "title": "River Medway"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You can <a href=\"/guidance/anglian-waterways-river-conditions-closures-and-restrictions\">check conditions, closures and restrictions on Anglian Waterways</a>.</p>\n\n<p>You should read the <a href=\"/government/publications/recreational-waterways-byelaws-anglian-region\">recreational bylaws</a> before you set out.</p>\n\n<p>You can also download information about facilities and safety for the following rivers:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/guidance/black-sluice-navigation-locks-and-facilities\">Black Sluice</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/guidance/river-ancholme-bridge-heights-locks-and-facilities\">River Ancholme</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/guidance/rivers-welland-and-glen-locks-and-facilities\">River Welland and Glen</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/guidance/river-great-ouse-bridge-heights-locks-and-facilities\">River Great Ouse</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/guidance/river-nene-bridge-heights-locks-and-facilities\">River Nene</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/guidance/river-stour-locks-and-facilities\">River Stour</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "anglian-waterways",
        "title": "Anglian Waterways"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You can <a href=\"/guidance/rye-harbour-closures-and-restrictions\">check conditions, closures and restrictions at Rye Harbour</a>.</p>\n\n<p>You should also check the Rye Harbour:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/guidance/rye-harbour-passage-pilot-and-mooring-information-for-boaters\">passage, pilot and mooring information for boaters</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/government/publications/rye-harbour-and-river-rother-map\">map guide</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/government/publications/rye-harbour-byelaws\">bylaws</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "rye-harbour",
        "title": "Rye Harbour"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You can check:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://canalrivertrust.org.uk/notices\">river and canal closure information on Canal &amp; River Trust waterways in England</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.scottishcanals.co.uk/boating/ongoing-works\">canal works and closures on Scottish Canals</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.waterwaysireland.org/Pages/Marine-Notices.aspx\">river and canal restrictions and closures on Waterways Ireland</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "scotland-northern-ireland-and-other-parts-of-england",
        "title": "Scotland, Northern Ireland and other parts of England"
      }
    ]
  },
